Simple Personal Website Plan (Pages + Content Only)

Pages
- Home
  - Hero: name, role/title, 1-line value proposition
  - Primary CTA: Contact; Secondary: Projects or Resume
  - Highlights: 3 flagship projects (title, 1–2 line impact, stack, links)
  - Skills snapshot: 5–10 key skills grouped (e.g., Languages, Frameworks, Data/ML)
  - Experience snapshot: 2–3 roles with one metric-driven bullet each
  - Social links: GitHub, LinkedIn, Email

- Projects
  - Intro: one sentence about what you build and enjoy
  - For each project:
    - Title and short tagline (outcome-oriented)
    - 2–4 bullets with measurable results (before → after where possible)
    - Tech stack tags
    - Links: GitHub, Live Demo, Case Study (optional)
  - Optional: filter by category (All, Data/ML, Web, Automation)

- About
  - Short bio (3–5 sentences): who you are, focus areas, impact, what you’re seeking
  - What I do now: 3–5 focus areas or services
  - Selected experience: compact list with 1 impact bullet per role
  - Education/Certifications (one-liners)
  - Personal/volunteering interests (optional, brief)

- Resume
  - Download latest PDF (link)
  - Optional inline summary: top 3 achievements or skills

- Contact
  - Openness: roles/opportunities you’re open to
  - Email button and LinkedIn link
  - Optional contact form: name, email, message

Optional Sections/Pages
- Blog: 3–5 posts that showcase depth (problem → approach → results → lessons)
- Testimonials: 2–3 quotes with names/titles/company
- Speaking/Writing: talks, publications, posts with links
- Open Source: notable repos and contributions

Content Formulas (to keep copy concise and impactful)
- Project bullet: <Action> <what> using <tools>, resulting in <metric> (<before> → <after>).
- Experience bullet: <Improved/Built/Led> <system/process> for <audience>, achieving <metric> using <method/tools>.

That’s it—no architecture or technical details included in this plan.# Personal Site Plan (Sections + Content)

Goal: Turn resume content into a clear, scannable, metrics-driven personal website. Primary audiences: recruiters/hiring managers, collaborators/clients.

---

## Information Architecture
- Pages: Home, Projects, About, Resume (PDF), Blog (optional), Contact
- Global Nav: Home • Projects • About • Blog • Contact
- Footer: Email • LinkedIn • GitHub • Location • Copyright
- CTAs: "Contact Me", "View Resume", "Book a Call" (choose one primary)

---

## Sections (Home Page)

1) Hero
- Purpose: 5-second pitch + primary CTA
- Content:
  - Headline: "<Role/Title> specializing in <domains>"
  - Subhead: "I build <outcomes> using <skills/tools>—impacting <metrics>."
  - Primary CTA: "Contact Me"; Secondary CTA: "View Projects" or "Download Resume"
  - Quick Links: GitHub • LinkedIn • Email

2) Credibility Bar (Optional)
- Logos: employers, clients, publications, conferences, or notable affiliations
- Alternative: key numbers ("8+ years", "5 deployed products", "$X saved")

3) Highlight Projects (Top 3)
- For each: title, 1–2 line impact summary, 3–5 bullet highlights
- Include metrics (speedups, revenue, adoption, accuracy, uptime, cost savings)
- Buttons: "Case Study" and/or "GitHub"

4) Experience Snapshot
- 2–4 roles condensed with quantifiable outcomes
- Format: Company • Title • Dates • 1–2 achievement bullets with metrics
- Link: "View full experience" → About page

5) Skills Matrix
- Grouped by category: Languages, Frameworks, Data/ML, Cloud/DevOps, Tools
- Emphasize depth and recency; optionally tag with proficiency or years

6) Testimonials (Optional)
- 1–3 short quotes from managers/peers/clients with names/titles

7) Contact / CTA Section
- Short invite: "Open to <roles/opportunities>"
- Email button, calendar link (if applicable), social links

