## Writing Prompts (to extract metrics from your resume)
- What improved? Time, cost, accuracy, reliability, revenue, adoption, latency, throughput
- How much? %, absolute values, counts, ranges
- For whom? users, teams, customers, regions
- How validated? A/B tests, benchmarks, revenue reports, incident counts

---

## Visual/Brand Guidelines
- Tone: clean, professional, accessible
- Palette: 1 primary, 1 accent, neutral grays
- Typography: readable sans-serif; consistent sizes/scale
- Imagery: product screenshots, charts, tasteful code snippets

---

## Technical Plan (suggested)
- Stack: Static site (Next.js or Astro) or simple Flask/HTML if preferred
- Data-driven content: YAML/JSON files for projects and experience
- Components: Hero, ProjectCard, SkillsGrid, ExperienceList, ContactForm
- Performance: static export, image optimization, lazy-loading
- Analytics: lightweight (e.g., Plausible), cookie-less if possible
- SEO: metadata per page, Open Graph images, sitemap, robots.txt

---

## Accessibility & Performance Checklist
- Color contrast AA+, focus states, keyboard nav
- Semantic HTML landmarks, alt text, labels
- Lighthouse: Performance ≥ 90, Accessibility ≥ 95
- Image optimization (responsive sizes, modern formats)

---

## Deployment
- Options: GitHub Pages, Vercel, Netlify, or S3/CloudFront
- CI: on push to main → build → deploy
- Custom domain + HTTPS

---

## Content Inventory (to prepare)
- Latest resume PDF (export, tagged for accessibility)
- Headshot (optional), logos/screenshots (approved for use)
- Links: GitHub repos, live demos, notebooks, talks
- 3–5 flagship projects with metrics and visuals
- 2–4 condensed experience bullets with numbers

---

## Roadmap
- Phase 1: Content
  - Finalize hero, 3 flagship projects, experience snapshot, skills, contact
- Phase 2: Build
  - Scaffold project, implement components, load content from data files
- Phase 3: Polish
  - SEO, analytics, performance, accessibility, responsive testing
- Phase 4: Ship
  - Connect domain, set up CI/CD, post-launch checklist

